  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nToday Qute use StringBuilder as output and returns the generated String to the client. IMHO I think it should be better to use the HTPP response Writer to write the Qute render result.\r\n\r\nIt will improve memory performance to avoid storing the String result of the render on server side.\r\n\r\nFor Qute debugging support with breakpint in an Editor/IDE , it should be nice because user could see the result on the webbrowser according to the breakpoint that he set.\r\n\r\n### Implementation ideas\r\n\r\nThe Template#render should provide a new signature with Writer to write the render result in the Writer (ex : HTTP response Writer).",
